! 2015-08-03 - Manuel Tobias Schiller
 - patch to PrPixelTrack on behalf of Daniel CÃ¡mpora <danielcampora@gmail.com>:
   I added some vectorization code at some point, which broke when the hits
   were changed to store wx and wy instead of wx^2 and wy^2 in the error
   values of the hits. The vectorized code was relying on x,y,z,wx stored
   consecutively in memory, but assumed wx to be wx^2.
   Here is a fix for that then, preserving wx and wy in whatever form they
   may be, and accessing their values by the method wx() and wy().

